articles.title: The “Weird Shrimp From Canada” Likely Much Weaker Than Once Assumed - SciTechDaily
articles.description: New biomechanical research reveals that Anomalocaris canadensis was speedy, but not strong enough to crack trilobite shells. New research on the extinct marine predator Anomalocaris canadensis disputes its status as an apex predator during the Cambrian era. U…
articles.content: A biomechanical study suggests that the extinct marine animal Anomalocaris canadensis, once considered an apex predator during the Cambrian era, may not have been as powerful as previously believed. … [+4461 chars]
